headline: Lennar posts lower quarterly profit on sustained market weakness
summary: Lennar Corp reported lower first-quarter profit on Thursday, as high mortgage rates and house prices deterred potential buyers, sending shares down 4% after the bell.  "While demand remains strong, persistently higher interest rates and inflation, combined with a downturn in consumer confidence and a limited supply of affordable homes, made it increasingly difficult for consumers to access homeownership," said co-CEO Stuart Miller.  For the first quarter ended February 28, Lennar reported a decline in average sales price to $408,000, 1% lower than last year, reflecting continued weakness in the market.

headline: Lennar: Fiscal Q1 Earnings Snapshot
summary: MIAMI (AP) — Lennar Corp. LEN) on Thursday reported fiscal first-quarter earnings of $519.5 million. On a per-share basis, the Miami-based company said it had net income of $1.96.
